"script": "She glanced down at her phone for just one second to read a single text. The road was straight, the day was clear, and she'd done it a hundred times before. But in that one second, at highway speed, her car drifted the length of a football field. And when she finally looked up, the curve was already on top of her. There was no time to brake, no time to scream. The text she'd risked everything to read said only, almost home. Investigators found the message still glowing on her cracked screen, sent by the family now waiting for her.",
